devdoc.details: Contract to manage the claiming of ROLU rewards by users. Users claim rewards based on a signature provided by a trusted backend admin. The contract pulls tokens from a designated treasury address upon successful claim verification.

ECDSAInvalidSignatureLength(uint256).details: The signature has an invalid length.

ECDSAInvalidSignatureS(bytes32).details: The signature has an S value that is in the upper half order.

NonceAlreadyClaimed().details: Thrown when the nonce has already been used.

OwnableInvalidOwner(address).details: The owner is not a valid owner account. (eg. `address(0)`)

OwnableUnauthorizedAccount(address).details: The caller account is not authorized to perform an operation.

TransferFailed().details: Thrown when the ERC20 transferFrom fails.

ZeroClaimAmount().details: Thrown when the claim amount is zero.

AdminAddressUpdated(address,address).details: Emitted when the admin address is updated.

RewardsClaimed(address,uint256,uint256).details: Emitted when a user successfully claims rewards.

params.amountWei: The amount of ROLU claimed (in wei).
params.nonce: The nonce used for this claim verification.
params.user: The address of the user claiming rewards.

claimRewards(uint256,uint256,bytes).details: Verifies a signature provided by the backend admin before transferring tokens. The signature must correspond to a hash of the claimant's address, the amount, and a unique nonce.

params._amountWei: The total amount of ROLU tokens to claim (in wei, 1e18 format).
params._nonce: A unique nonce provided by the backend for this claim attempt.
params._signature: The EIP-712 style signature from the admin address.

params._adminAddress: The address authorized to sign claim messages.
params._initialOwner: The initial owner of this contract.
params._roluTokenAddress: The address of the ROLU ERC20 token contract.
params._treasuryAddress: The address holding the ROLU tokens to be distributed.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params._amount: The amount of ROLU tokens to withdraw.
